2. Language as Interface Layer

Language operates as the outer interface layer for meaning transmission between minds.

experience → cognition → language → transmission → new cognition

Language compresses and transports meaning across individuals and generations.

⸻

3. Metaphor as Multi-Channel Encoding

Metaphor allows simultaneous activation of multiple neural networks:
	•	emotion
	•	imagery
	•	reasoning
	•	memory

Thus metaphor functions as high-bandwidth semantic compression.

